02) Proceedings of the Fourth International Conference on Gas Hydrates, pp. 780-784. , Yokohama; Sloan, E.D., Fleyfel, F., Hydrate dissociation enthalpy and guest size (1992) Fluid Phase Equilib., 76, pp. 123-140; Yoon, J.H., Yamamoto, Y., Komai, T., Haneda, H., Rigorous approach to the prediction of the heat of dissociation of gas hydrates (2003) Ind. Eng. Chem. Res., 42, pp. 1111-1114; Carroll, J.J., Slupsky, J.D., Mather, A.E., The solubility of carbon dioxide in water at low pressure (1991) J. Phys. Chem. Ref. Data, 20, pp. 1201-1209; Yoon, J.H., Chun, M.K., Lee, H., Generalized model for predicting phase behavior of clathrate hydrate (2002) AIChE J., 48, pp. 1317-1330; Anderson, G.K., Enthalpy of dissociation and hydration number of carbon dioxide hydrate from the clapeyron equation (2003) J. Chem. Thermodyn., 35, pp. 1169-1181; Uchida, T., Physical property measurements on CO2 clathrate hydrates. Review of crystallography, hydration number, and mechanical properties (1997) Waste Manage., 17, pp. 343-352; Uchida, T., Ebinuma, T., Narita, H., Observations of CO2-hydrate decomposition and reformation processes (2000) J. Cryst. Growth, 217, pp. 189-200; Circone, S., Stern, L.A., Kirby, S.H., Durham, W.B., Chakoumakos, B.C., Rawn, C.J., Rondinone, A.J., Ishii, Y., CO2 hydrate: Synthesis, composition, structure, dissociation behavior, and a comparison to structure I CH4 hydrate (2003) J. Phys. Chem. B, 107, pp. 5529-5539; Morgan, J.J., Blackwell, V.R., Johnson, D.E., Spencer, D.F., North, W.J., Hydrate formation from gaseous CO2 and water (1999) Environ. Sci. Technol., 33, pp. 1448-1452; North, W.J., Blackwell, V.R., Morgan, J.J., Studies of CO2 hydrate formation and dissolution (1998) Environ. Sci. Technol., 32, pp. 676-681; Kawamura, T., Komai, T., Yamamoto, Y., Nagashima, K., Ohga, K., Higuchi, K., Growth kinetics of CO2 hydrate just below melting point of ice (2002) J. Cryst. Growth, 234, pp. 200-226","Delahaye, A.; Cemagref-GPAN, Parc de Tourvoie, B.P. 44, 9216